def sum_x_y(x, y):
    sum = 0
    for i in range(len(x)):
        sum =+ sum + x[i]*y[i]
    return sum
def sum_x(x):
    sum = 0
    for i in range(len(x)):
        sum =+ sum + x[i]
    return sum
def sum_x_square(x):
    sum = 0
    for i in range(len(x)):
        sum =+ sum + x[i]**2
    return sum
# Y X
m_y, m_x = np.mean(y), np.mean(x)

#    
b1_y_x = (len(x)*sum_x_y(x, y) - sum_x(x)*sum_x(y))/(len(x)*sum_x_square(x) - sum_x(x)**2)
b0_y_x = m_y - b1_y_x*m_x
print(f"  Y  X: Y = {b0_y_x} + ({b1_y_x}) * X")

  Y  X: Y = 18.584386719121436 + (-0.9357807730176725) * X

def Q_y(y):
    sum = 0 
    My=np.mean(y)
    for i in range(len(y)):
        sum = sum + (y[i]-My)**2
    return sum

R_2 = 1 - S(x,y)*(len(x) - 2)/Q_y(y)
print('  R\u00B2= ', R_2)

  R=  0.7574752435457786

G_right_b_0 = b0_y_x + sts.t.ppf(1-alpha/2,n-2)*s*np.sqrt(sum_x_square(x)/(Q_x*n))

G_left_b_1 = b1_y_x - sts.t.ppf(1-alpha/2,n-2)*s*np.sqrt(1/(Q_x))
